It's an age old tradition on the streets of Catalonia in Spain, but not one that the average Londoner expects to see on their lunch break.

More than 170 members of the Human Towers de Vilafranca team clambered on top of one another to make their UK debut this afternoon in an attempt to build a living structure to rival Tower Bridge.

Not a hobby likely to endear itself to health and safety officials, the stunt saw members of the team - men, women and children of all ages and sizes - climb barefoot on the shoulders of their colleagues reaching higher and higher.

