The tradition is kept alive by some 7,000 castellers who belong to 66 different teams.

As well as performing close to London Bridge, the Human Towers de Vilafranca team also showcased their talents in Moorgate and will perform at Clapham Common, the Millennium Bridge in Southwark and Borough Market throughout the weekend.

The group performed their daring stunt on top of a building in Manhattan last summer to commemorate the ongoing rebuilding of the World Trade Center.

